{{Infobox member of the Knesset |image = Boaz Toporovsky.JPG |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1980|7|17|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Rishon LeZion]], [[Israel]] |death_date = |death_place = |Knesset(s) = [[Israeli legislative election, 2013|19]] |party1 = [[Yesh Atid]] |partyyears1 = 2013–2015 |minister1 = }}
'''Boaz Toporovsky''' ({{lang-he|בועז טופורובסקי}}, born 17 July 1980) is an [[Israel]]i politician. He served as a member of the [[Knesset]] for [[Yesh Atid]] between 2013 and 2015.
==Biography== Toporovsky was born and grew up in [[Rishon LeZion]]. After completing his mandatory military service in the [[Israel Defense Forces]], he studied law at [[Tel Aviv University]]. During his studies, Toporovsky became chairman of the university's student union in 2005, holding the post until 2007. He then entered politics and worked for Minister of Social Affairs, [[Isaac Herzog]].<ref>[http://www.haaretz.com/news/national/new-kids-in-the-knesset-lapid-s-activists.premium-1.496016 New kids in the Knesset: Lapid’s activists] Haaretz, 24 January 2013</ref>
In 2008 he became chairman of the [[National Union of Israeli Students]], and in the same year founded the Tzabar party, heading its list for the [[Israeli legislative election, 2009|2009 Knesset elections]], in which it received only 0.14% of the vote and failed to pass the electoral threshold. However, the party did win seats on [[Tel Aviv]] city council.<ref>[http://www.timesofisrael.com/yair-lapids-sends-a-diverse-quality-slate-to-knesset/ All the kingmaker’s men, and women] Times of Israel, 23 January 2013</ref> In March 2011 he became chairman of the [[Issta]] travel agency.
In the [[Israeli legislative election, 2013|2013 Knesset elections]] he was placed eighteenth on [[Yesh Atid]]'s list, becoming a Knesset member when the party won 19 seats. He was placed fourteenth on the party's list for the [[Israeli legislative election, 2015|2015 elections]],<ref>[http://www.bechirot20.gov.il/election/Candidates/Pages/OneListCandidates.aspx?LPF=Search&WebId=6adadc15-e476-480b-9746-04490aedeb0f&ListID=ba72a662-765c-45af-9d48-fb68080956af&ItemID=43&FieldID=ListNickname_GxS_Text Yesh Atid list] Central Elections Committee</ref> losing his seat as the party was reduce to 11 seats.
Toporovsky is married to Shelly Herman, participant of the third season of Israeli reality show [[MasterChef Israel|Master Chef]].
