{{Infobox person | name = Clément Fayat | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth based on age as of date |85|2017|04|27}}<ref name="forbes1">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/clement-fayat/ |title=Clement Fayat & family |publisher=Forbes.com |accessdate=2017-04-27}}</ref> | birth_place = France | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | restingplace = | nationality = French | residence = [[Saint-Émilion]], France | education = | alma mater = | occupation = businessman | title = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | known for = founder and owner, [[Fayat Group]] | boards = | salary = | networth = US$2.1 billion (April 2017)<ref name="forbes1"/> | spouse = married | children = | parents = | relations = | website = }}
'''Clément Fayat''' (born 1931/32) is a French [[billionaire]] entrepreneur, who founded [[Fayat Group]] at the age of 25.<ref name="forbes1"/>
Fayat is the son of a bricklayer, and left school at 15 to become a construction apprentice. He founded the civil engineering company [[Fayat Group]] when he was 25, and it is now France's largest privately-held construction and civil engineering company, with 19,000 staff in 120 countries.<ref name="forbes1"/>
Fayat is married and lives in [[Saint-Émilion]], France.<ref name="forbes1"/>
