The British Association of '''Communicators in Business''' (CiB) is a professional body based in the [[United Kingdom]] which provides in-house, freelance and agency staff involved in [[internal communications]].

It aims to provide support for professionals involved in strategy planning and delivery, writing, design, online, print, measurement and brand management, among other internal communication disciplines.

On 23 September 2009 the members of CiB voted to change the name and status of the association to the Institute of Internal Communication (IoIC). The official changeover to Institute status, along with the launch of its new corporate identity, will take place at their annual conference in May 2010.<ref>[http://www.communicatemagazine.co.uk/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=428:cib-votes-for-name-change&catid=1:stories&Itemid=115 CiB votes for name change] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008045615/http://www.communicatemagazine.co.uk/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=428%3Acib-votes-for-name-change&catid=1%3Astories&Itemid=115 |date=8 October 2011 }} Communicate magazine, 2009-09-24</ref>

